title: decrease
rationale: All predicates that imply a decrease in a quantified measure.

title: increase
rationale: All predicates that imply a increase in a quantified measure.

title: no_increase_or_decrease
rationale: All predicates that imply a lack of quantifiable effect on a measure.

title: broadened
rationale: All predicates that imply an increase or expansion in scope, width, or range.

title: narrowed
rationale: All predicates that imply a decrease, restriction, or narrowing in scope, width, or range.

title: increase_in_speed
rationale: All predicates that imply an increase or acceleration in speed or rate.

title: decrease_in_speed
rationale: All predicates that imply a decrease, deceleration, or delay in speed or rate.

title: decrease_in_duration
rationale: All predicates that imply a reduction or shortening in duration or length.

title: increase_in_duration
rationale: All predicates that imply an increase, extension, or prolongation in duration or length.

title: bind
rationale: All predicates that imply the subject is able to or has formed a binding interaction with the object.

title: not_bind
rationale: All predicates that imply the subject is unable to or has not formed a binding interaction with the object.

title: join
rationale: All predicates that imply that the subject joined the objects into a complex or group.

title: break
rationale: All predicates that imply that the subject broke the objects apart, separated or did not combine them.

title: coordination
rationale: Predicates that imply the coordination or organization of processes or events.

title: disorganization
rationale: Predicates that imply the diruption of coordination of processes or events.

title: establishment
rationale: All predicates that imply the establishment or confirmation of a finding.

title: prevention_of_establishment
rationale: All predicates that imply the refutation of a finding.

title: negative_correlation
rationale: All predicates that imply a negative or inverse relationship between variables.

title: positive_correlation
rationale: All predicates that imply a positive or direct relationship between variables.

title: no_correlation
rationale: All predicates that explicitly state the absence of a correlation between variables.

title: reach_maximum
rationale: All predicates that imply reaching the highest or peak value.

title: reach_minimum
rationale: All predicates that imply reaching the lowest or trough value.

title: critical
rationale: Predicates that imply something is essential or necessary for a process or outcome.

title: not_critical
rationale: Predicates that imply something is not essential or not necessary for a process or outcome.

title: sufficient
rationale: Predicates that imply something is sufficient or adequate for a process or outcome.

title: not_sufficient
rationale: Predicates that imply something is not sufficient or not adequate for a process or outcome.

title: encoded_by
rationale: All predicates that imply the subject is encoded by the object.

title: not_encoded_by
rationale: All predicates that imply the subject is not encoded by the object.

title: detect
rationale: All predicates that imply the presence or detection of something.

title: not_detect
rationale: All predicates that imply the absence of detection of something.

title: linked
rationale: All predicates that imply the existence of an arbitrary association between subject and object.

title: not_linked
rationale: All predicates that imply the absence of an association between subject and object.

title: give_medical_care
rationale: All predicates that imply giving medical care or attention.

title: not_give_medical_care
rationale: All predicates that imply not giving medical care or attention.

title: predict
rationale: All predicates that imply the ability to predict or make accurate forecasts.

title: not_predict
rationale: All predicates that imply the inability to predict or make accurate forecasts.

title: serve_as
rationale: All predicates that imply the subject served or could serve the function or role.

title: not_serve_as
rationale: All predicates that imply the subject did not serve or could not serve the function or role.

title: select
rationale: All predicates that indicate the subject has been chosen or picked.

title: not_select
rationale: All predicates that indicate the subject has not been chosen or picked.

title: contain
rationale: All predicates that imply the presence or inclusion of something.

title: not_contain
rationale: All predicates that imply the absence or exclusion of something.

title: precede
rationale: All predicates that imply the subject precedes the object in space or time.

title: follow
rationale: All predicates that imply the subject follows the object in space or time.

title: employ
rationale: All predicates that indicate the subject was used to achieve a goal.

title: not_employ
rationale: All predicates that imply the subject is not employed.

title: admit
rationale: All predicates that imply the admission or acceptance of something.

title: not_admit
rationale: All predicates that imply lack of admission of something.

title: genetic_correlation
rationale: All predicates that imply the existence of a genetic correlation between subject and object.
predicates: was a genetic risk factor for

title: no_genetic_correlation
rationale: All predicates that explicitly state the absence of a genetic correlation between subject and object.
predicates: was not a genetic risk factor for

title: exhibit
rationale: All predicates that imply the presence, showing, or manifestation of a property or behavior.

title: not_exhibit
rationale: All predicates that imply the absence, lack, or non-manifestation of a property or behavior.

title: replacement
rationale: All predicates that imply the act of replacing one entity with another.

title: no_replacement
rationale: All predicates that explicitly state the absence of replacement.

title: identification
rationale: All predicates that imply identification of a fact.

title: lack_of_identification
rationale: All predicates that imply lack of identification.

title: upregulated
rationale: All predicates that imply an increase or upregulation in gene or protein expression.

title: downregulated
rationale: All predicates that imply a decrease or downregulation in gene or protein expression.

title: production
rationale: All predicates that imply the creation or production of something.

title: degradation
rationale: All predicates that imply the deconstruction of something.

title: appear
rationale: All predicates that imply something is emerging or appearing.

title: disappear
rationale: All predicates that imply something is disappearing.

title: effect
rationale: All predicates that imply an effect or influence is present.

title: no_effect
rationale: All predicates that explicitly state absence of effect or influence.

title: positive_causation
rationale: All predicates that imply the subject has a causal, contributory, or enabling effect on the object that is not explicitly positive or negative.

title: negative_causation
rationale: All predicates that imply the subject prevents or counteracts the effects of the object.

title: localize
rationale: All predicates that imply localization or targeting of the subject to a specific location or context.

title: not_localize
rationale: All predicates that explicitly state the absence of localization or targeting.

title: vaccinate
rationale: All predicates that imply the subject has received a vaccination.

title: not_vaccinate
rationale: All predicates that imply the subject has not received a vaccination.

title: has_capacity
rationale: All predicates that imply the ability, potential, or capacity to perform an action or exhibit a property.

title: lacks_capacity
rationale: All predicates that imply the absence of ability, potential, or capacity to perform an action or exhibit a property.

title: positive_effect_on_unfavourable_condition
rationale: All predicates that imply an improvement of an unfavourable condition.

title: negative_effect_on_unfavourable_condition
rationale: All predicates that imply the worsening of an unfavourable condition.

title: negative_judgemental_effect
rationale: All predicates that imply a worsening of outcome on the scale of undesired-desired relative to a neutral baseline.

title: positive_judgemental_effect
rationale: All predicates that imply an improvement of outcome on the scale of undesired-desired relative to a neutral baseline.
